    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-08T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="388"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/25080a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-08T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 8, 1921—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>101. Whereas the consul at Tampico reported on July 1 [<hi rend="italic">June
                        30</hi>] that he feared anti-American outbreaks because of the unemployment
                    growing out of the cessation of oil shipments, orders were issued for warships
                    to proceed to that port. Since the fears were <pb facs="0547" n="451"
                        xml:id="pg_451"/> shown to be baseless, and the lives and property of
                    American citizens do not appear now to be endangered, the vessels have been
                    ordered to leave that port.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
